Bob Geren was fired today as manager
of the  Oakland Athletics , who have lost nine games in a row and
fallen into last place in the American League West.  Bob Melvin, a broadcaster and former manager of the Arizona
Diamondbacks, was appointed to fill the job for the rest of this
season by General Manager Billy Beane.  Geren, 49, had a 334-376 record since taking over as the
Aâ€™s manager in November 2006. Oakland is 27-36 this season.  The changes were announced by the Major League Baseball
